urls.title: All Nippon Airways (@allnipponairways) • Instagram photo
urls.description: All Nippon Airways shared a post on Instagram: "We asked, and you answered! Thank you for sharing your travels with us to celebrate 70 years in the air! Our story today is from IG user @shortysmama68: #MyANAStory really began the moment my 2 brothers, my boyfriend and I stepped on board the ANA Dreamliner from Honolulu to Narita in October of 2018. We flew Business Class and were treated like royalty by everyone we came into contact with. We each had our own flight attendants who catered to our every need. When our plane arrived at the gate, we were met by this ANA ramp agent bowing respectfully to the plane. It seemed like this was not just an arriving plane full of passengers to him, but a wonderful company that he is proud to be a part of. The bow demonstrates he is thankful for the arriving passengers and their safe arrival. I shed a tear when I saw this. I am so glad I was able to capture the moment. I am thankful that I was able to experience Japan. #FlyANA #AllNipponAirways". Fo

data.text:

Thank you for sharing your ANA story with us! https://t.co/V0gBVFi1ip

urls.description: [ANA official] The Izumo Grand Shrine is a shrine registered as a World Heritage site located in Taisha Town, Izumo City in Shimane Prefecture. This is one of the major shrines in Japan. Its amulets and goshuin (shrine's seal stamped onto a notebook) are very popular, and the shrine is also known for its god of matchmaking. There are lots of restaurants serving Izumo soba noodles in the neighborhood, so the areas surrounding the shrine are also not to be missed. ANA introduces great spots in shimane Prefecture with text and photographs.
